        gdocType: "article",
        xhtml:
          '<sticky-right>\n  <left>\n    <text>In the chart, you can see the estimated prevalence of people who meet the criteria to be diagnosed with each category of mental illness, as they are classified by the ICD manual.</text>\n    <text>As you can see, anxiety disorders and depressive disorders are more common. It’s estimated that around 3–4% of people worldwide have had them in the past year.</text>\n    <text>Bipolar disorder, schizophrenia and eating disorders are less common. For example, it’s estimated that 0.3% of people have schizophrenia worldwide.</text>\n  </left>\n  <right>\n    <chart url="https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/share-of-population-with-mental-illnesses"/>\n  </right>\n</sticky-right>',
